ne directly in the management of not only society but also the natural environment. As most arable, accessible land in British Columbia was already being farmed by 1919, the state had to undertake environmental engineering projects on a scale not yet attempted in the province. Creating a Modern Countryside examines how this process unfolded, identifies its successes and failures, and demonstrates how the human-environment relationship of the early twentieth century shaped the province as it is today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnvironmental economicszBritish ColumbiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aEnvironmental policyzBritish ColumbiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLand settlementzBritish ColumbiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLand use, RuralzBritish ColumbiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLiberalismzBritish ColumbiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aRural renewalzBritish ColumbiaxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh1 aWynn, Graeme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485583940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774855839423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774855839/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles